Rating: 3
My twelve year old daughter and I made this together. We doubled the recipe to fit our ice cream maker and ended up with two pies - one for a party and one for us. Everyone thought it was delicious, but the crust was very difficult to cut. I think it needed to bake for longer, maybe twelve minutes or so, which I'll try next time. We thought the ice cream mixture would also make a wonderful lemon pudding, if thickened properly. We'll try that at a later time.

